Package: cardioPredictR
Title: Cardiovascular Disease Risk Classification Using Random Forest
Version: 1.0.0
Author: Haotian Yang [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Haotian Yang <Haotian.Yang22@student.xjtlu.edu.cn>
Description: 
    Provides a reproducible R package for classifying cardiovascular disease
    (CVD) risk using a trained Random Forest model. The package exports a single
    prediction function that accepts patient-level clinical data and returns
    categorical risk labels (Low Risk / High Risk). The predictive model and
    feature engineering pipeline are consistent with those used in the
    accompanying Shiny application, ensuring reproducible results across
    different computing environments.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    ranger,
    dplyr,
    stats
